Package excelExporter.excelParser.dataModel

Enum Class Cluster.PseudoFieldName

Enclosing class:
Cluster
public static enum Cluster.PseudoFieldName extends Enum<Cluster.PseudoFieldName>
This is the list of pseudo-fields of class Cluster that can be accessed from a StringTemplate V4 template. The enumerated fields can be accessed like ordinary public fields from a StringTemplate V4 template. The dot notation is used to do so. Taking the first named value theOnlyWorkbook as an example, one would write <cluster.theOnlyWorkbook> to access the related pseudo-field.

A short explanation of each pseudo-field and a reference to more in-depth information can be found as description of each named value of the enumeration.

Please note, that the pseudo-fields of the base class ObjectMap are inherited and can be accessed, too. See ObjectMap.PseudoFieldName.

A detailed discussion of pseudo-fields and the enumeration of these can be found in the class description of ObjectMap.

    • bookAry

      public static final Cluster.PseudoFieldName bookAry
      The list of all parsed workbooks. This pseudo-field is an alias to access the pseudo-field ObjectMap.PseudoFieldName.itemAry of the base class.

      From a StringTemplate V4 template the list would be accessed with an expression like <cluster.bookAry>.

    • noBooks

      public static final Cluster.PseudoFieldName noBooks
      The number of parsed workbooks in the cluster. This pseudo-field is an alias to access the pseudo-field ObjectMap.PseudoFieldName.noItems.

      The number of books relates to both collections, ObjectMap.itemAry and ObjectMap.itemMap.

      From a StringTemplate V4 template the number would be accessed with an expression like <cluster.noBooks>.

    • sheetGroupMap

      public static final Cluster.PseudoFieldName sheetGroupMap
      The parsed worksheets can be kept in global groups of those (and regardless of their relationship to workbooks). Here's the map Cluster.sheetGroupMap of these groups and lookup is done by the name of the group.

      From a StringTemplate V4 template the map of groups would be accessed with an expression like <cluster.sheetGroupMap>.
